# Cartographer — business directory profile

_Last updated: (date) by (you or cartographer)_

The cartographer reads this before every run. You can edit it by hand at any
time; keep it under ~150 lines.

## What counts as a business here

- A business is anything OSM tags as amenity / shop / tourism / office / craft /
  leisure that has a name — but WHAT to scan and in WHICH ORDER is governed by
  the tier ranking in data/config/categories.json (hand-editable, read each run).
- Tiers: 1 = scan first, 2 = next, 3 = next. Tier 4 is NOT businesses (parking,
  benches, pitches, toilets…) — NEVER scan it; it only wastes budget.
- Chains (OSM brand tag) are still captured, but forced to lowest priority and
  hidden in the directory — don't go out of your way to scan them.

## Towns and tiers to prioritize

- (List the towns from the region briefing, e.g. Rockland, Camden, Thomaston…)
- (Note any town where the admin-area name query fails and a bbox works better.)
- Scan order within a town: Tier 1 categories first, then Tier 2, then Tier 3 —
  never Tier 4. Target a tier-1/2 category directly or scan a whole key and keep
  only the tiers you want.

## Coverage (standing instructions)

- notes/coverage.md is the cursor: one line per (town × category) cell with the
  date scanned and the count. Each run, pick the never-scanned or stalest cells
  next, in tier-priority order (Tier 1 before Tier 2 before Tier 3).
- Query ONE business key per overpass_query call. If a cell comes back
  truncated, narrow it (smaller bbox or a more specific tag) and re-query.
- A business missing from a scan is not proof it closed — only mark closed/unknown
  inside a cell you fully scanned, and note it.
